---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Adam"
  description="Hello, my name is Adam. I'm a passionate runner who builds websites for a living. I decided to put those two skills together to create this blog."
>
  <section class="w-full max-w-128 mx-auto px-6 py-8 md:p-0 md:pt-12">
    <h1 class="font-[700] text-3xl text-elba -tracking-[1.25px]">
      Hello, my name is Adam.
    </h1>
    <p
      class="text-philippine-grey text-xl leading-[27.5px] -tracking-[.5px] font-serif mt-[4px]"
    >
      I'm a passionate runner who builds websites for a living. I decided to put
      those two skills together to create this blog.
    </p>

    <div
      class="w-full h-[300px] bg-philippine-grey z-20 relative rounded mt-4 bg-cover bg-position-[50%_100%]"
      style={{
        backgroundImage: `url('/images/adam_mckenna_running.jpg')`,
      }}
    >
    </div>
    <p class="text-philippine-grey text-xs font-light mt-2">
      At the&nbsp;
      <a
        class="text-sea-blue underline"
        href="https://www.parkrun.org.uk/blythlinks/"
        target="_blank">Blyth Links Parkrun</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section
    class="bg-white w-full min-h-[400px] -mt-[150px] px-6 pt-8 pb-12 md:p-0 md:pb-8"
  >
    <div
      class="grid gap-4 w-full max-w-128 mx-auto pt-32 md:pt-[172px] md:pb-8"
    >
      <p class="text-elba leading-[1.6] tracking-[-.25px]">
        <span class="font-semibold">I started running in 2017.</span> Like most people
        from North East England, my running journey began with the&nbsp;
        <a
          class="text-sea-blue underline"
          href="https://www.greatrun.org/events/great-north-run/"
          target="_blank"
        >
          Great North Run</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p class="text-elba leading-[1.6] tracking-[-.25px]">
        Fast-forward to 2020, the bordem of lockdown inspired a flurry of
        running.
      </p>
      <p class="text-elba leading-[1.6] tracking-[-.25px]">
        By 2025, I had{" "}
        <span class="font-semibold"> ran marathons all over the world </span>
        , from&nbsp;
        <a
          href="https://www.strava.com/activities/13018814997"
          class="text-sea-blue underline"
          target="_blank"
        >
          Thailand</a
        >&nbsp;to&nbsp;
        <a
          href="https://www.strava.com/activities/10737248846"
          class="text-sea-blue underline"
          target="_blank"
        >
          New Zealand</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p class="text-elba leading-[1.6] tracking-[-.25px]">
        A "obligation" to run the local half-marathon has transformed into a
        deep passion: I <i>love</i> running.
      </p>
      <p class="text-elba leading-[1.6] tracking-[-.25px]">
        In particular, the{" "}
        <span class="font-semibold">
          science of running, nutrition and endurance
        </span>{" "}
        fascinates me.
      </p>
      <p class="text-elba leading-[1.6] tracking-[-.25px]">
        This blog explores that fascination.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
